reviews.review_text: Love Five Guys as they always have the best fries in town. absolutely crunchy outside and soft inside, just the right amount. You can customize your burger, and they never mess it up, plus the great fries. They are just a fav go-to place for a quick burger and fries. The fact that they give you free peanuts in shell and have their potato bags all around the store with the peanut oil which they fry it in just creates an awesome environment. Love the open kitchen and the fact that you can see the fries are cut right there, with skin in different shapes. Just so much better than many fast food chains. I just wish they were open longer hours and had more locations.

Five Guys is a burger paradise in the heart of Vancouver. What sets this joint apart is the fantastic ability to customize your burger just the way you like it. The sheer range of toppings and sauces available ensures that every burger is a unique and personalized experience. The staffs friendly and accommodating nature makes the customization process a breeze. The burgers themselves are absolute showstoppers. Juicy, flavorful, and made to perfection, these burgers are a testament to the quality of ingredients used. The melt-in-your-mouth experience is unmatched, and its evident that a lot of care goes into preparing each burger. Now, lets talk about the fries - theyre more than just a side dish, theyre an experience on their own. Crispy on the outside and perfectly tender on the inside, these fries are simply addictive. The fact that theyre hand-cut and made fresh right there adds an extra level of deliciousness. The ambiance is lively and inviting, adding to the overall enjoyment of the meal. Whether youre a solo diner or with a group of friends, the welcoming atmosphere makes every visit enjoyable. For a truly customizable and mouthwatering burger experience paired with some of the best fries around, Five Guys in Vancouver is the place to be. The quality, flavor, and the ability to make your burger your own truly sets it apart. A must-visit for burger enthusiasts.
Pretty solid burger  , juicy, good size and tasty. Love how any extras are included and also the free peanuts. The jalapenos also had a good   to them

Its expensive of course but youre guaranteed a delicious burger and fries every time so I think thats worth the price. Good char on the crumbley patty and great flavourful cheese. Plenty of seasoning on the fries too coating each and every one.

Classic burgers made well and served with perfect soft and crispy fries. The person at the till - Pardeep I believe is very calm kind and friendly. Overall well run and clean place. Enjoy the style of burgers with various toppings that they serve Cajun style fries over regular for sure

Delicious mushroom cheese burger! Spicy fries are out of this world, and you gotta get em. The service and speed are average, and the atmosphere is dirty and rushed, but thats what you would expect here, its a part of the experience to have a table and floor covered in peanuts, and they delivered on that. Go in here expecting great greasy burgers and you will be fully satisfied! I highly recommend it and will be returning for more greasy treats! Wheelchair accessibility: No stairs in the restaurant, easily accessible by the sidewalk.

Tried five guys for the very first time and I m super impressed. I don t eat meat so the veggie sandwich was a great option! I love that you can pick and choose your toppings. The portions sizes were generous and the staff at this location were very friendly! I will be back. Also the Cajun fries were so good!!!
I saw this place and was surprised I saw it. Then I realised there is a Five Guys down the street from where I live in Florida. The food was great and reminded me of In-n-Out Burger from California!

I am picky about my food, okay. This might very well be the only non-overpriced, non-pretentious burger in town that I thoroughly enjoy. Service is wonderful, on a couple occasions when - during a peak hour - our orders were mixed up, they more than made up for it.

First time eating at five guys, and it was the best burger I have ever had, did not disappoint, and I had very high expectations from word of mouth. This location staff were so friendly. Very fast didnt wait long for my food. I cant wait to go back!

Best burgers in town! I always come here when I want a hamburger, and I get impressed In my last visit, the gentleman who attended to us took the order and immediately he follow us to clean our table, the environment was also clean and chill, then I decided to take some peanuts before we took our meal, those peanuts are a hungry relief right before you eat your cheeseburger, they even not take a long time, food was fresh and good as every time I come. Thanks guys!
One of the best and most consistent burgers.  Ill try any burger place, but theirs is one of the best.  Enjoy

Great place to grab a burger and fries. Better than your typical fast food burger place. Got the bacon burger with lots of toppings to choose from. The regular size burgers are double patties while the small size are single. Also make sure to get the cajun fries the seasoning is delicious. Free peanuts while you wait for your order. Lots of indoor seating.
Absolutely fantastic! Amazing food. Ravinder took our order, and he was great! Very friendly, great service from him!

If you want to eat a real bacon cheese burger, I mean a real burger thats flavour gets better and better with every single bite. Until your sad because its all gone. So tonight take your significant other for the best burger you and them will ever eat in your lives. Get out of the house and get out to Five Guys. P.S. the burgers taste like old school rink burgers if you know what I mean. If you dont then theres one more reason to go try one tonight and see what your missing out on. L8tr everyone enjoy

Hamburger was great Very delicious and high-quality   . I would say better than a lot of hamburger restaurants. Another surprise is the fries gosh.. big portion Plus the free peanuts   !! No complaints MAN

Honestly best place to get a burger cause its taste like home made also if you get a single its a Double they always throw a few fries in the bag also LOVE THIS PLACE BEST BURGERS AROUND FIVE GUYS NEVER DISAPPOINTS

Ohhhh, man. I myself am a burger enthusiast, and I am always thrilled to come to Five Guys. They always know how to cook and serve. Fries were a bit salty, but it perfectly balanced the fatty taste from the burger. I always order my burger with some bacon in it, never regretted. They use peanut oil, so be careful with your allergies. They do bottomless refills on pop and unlimited supply of toasted peanuts. Peanuts, you would think. But it was ridiculous how many peanuts I had. At first, it doesnt feel anything special, then 10 minutes later, you are left with piles of peanut shells. I know its American chain, but you gotta enjoy this.

I ordered a hot dog as I cant eat too much and it was the perfect size. The taste was also very good. My friend who ordered a hamburger was surprised at how big the hamburger was. I would like to go there again if there is another opportunity because it tastes good and I can eat slowly.

I have eaten here a few times but wasnt leaving reviews at the time.  I love how they offer up roasted peanuts.  This visit they had them open to bring to your table. I was getting mine to go, so didnt try them on this visit but the past visit they were good.  I love their fries as well! This visit I was only getting a cheeseburger to go because it was close to dinner time.  I took my cheeseburger to go and upon arriving home about 20 minutes or so later the burger was still toasty.  :)  You can add your own customized toppings but I just the basic and love their burgers.  Just the way I like them.  I also realized I got the regular burger instead of the mini so it has 2 patties.  I had to skip dinner. :)   I appreciate this business as they are always so busy when I go and they are just hopping and hustling and everyone gets fed.  Thank you!
You guys have great food especially burger and fries! Your apitizers are also very good five guys definitely deserves more than five stars keep it up!

They are constantly giving good service. The fries are the best in town, because they are never from frozen potatoes. The burgers are delicious, the beef is high quality and they give you all the fixings you want everytime.

Very good burgers, only thing is that the place feels dirty, almost like McDonalds or burger king, the owner may consider changing staff for a better experience. The lady behind the counter has a face full of hatred no matter who comes in. Its just very unpleasant first impressions, where her English is very bad plus she acts angry when she doesnt understand your order. And its not just one girl, its whole staff acting angry, rude and in a bad mood. I want to receive my burger with a smile on their faces, but I felt like they want me to choke on my burger and never come back again.

Amazing burgers and hotdogs, plus free peanuts! Probably one of the best hotdogs I have had in a long time. Lunch time is busy but is generally easy to get seated. Definetely worth a stop if youre around Granville.

I love this burger & fries! I m not a big fan of fries, but this is on another level. Now I m a big fan of Five Guys fries :p Their topping selection is also great point- grilled mushrooms and onions are always the best. What makes me sad is they don t serve milkshakes-one of their featured one. When I was in US, I loved combos with all(burger, fries and milkshake). It takes some time to prepare the food, but it s worthy. Highly recommended!

This is my first burger in vancouver even in canada. Lots of local burgers here and I decided to order at five guys. I wasnt disappointed with the taste, its really good burger. Also their patty is juicy enough for me. The bun is soft. I have no regrets choosing five guys as the first burger I ate in Canada

As a place with the name burgers and fries, it better be really good at what they do. And they are very good. The burgers were moist and built with the exact toppings you want. The fries were well seasoned, crispy on the outside and soft on the inside (I highly recommend the cajun style fries). This place is essentially a step above fast food, fast food + if you will. Not quite as good as a steakhouse burger or a proper restaurant burger but would pick this over any of the typical fast food places any day. Prices are slightly more but you get exactly what you pay for, if not more.

If you want a quality Smashburger with quality ingredients and a solid assortment of topping options, this is the place for you. My only mild criticism is that sometimes they get in enough of a hurry that the cheese isnt completely melted.

The place was incredibly packed. The service was outstanding. The place was clean. The burgers and the hotdog were out of this world. The only thing I regret is not trying them out earlier. What a burger! What attention! Thank you!

I went to this place with my husband and we had a great time here! The employees were very swift and efficient! We did not have to wait long in spite of the place being crowded! The quality of their burger is top notch! And everything inside of it went amazingly together! The peanuts were an added bonus! The bathrooms were clean and hygienic! The place itself needs some tidying though.

Pros:  The food was delcious!  The Cajun fries were my personal favorite.  Staff was very friendly. Cons:  We visited as a BC Lions game ended, and the restaurant was extremely busy (giving the staff a little bit of a pass) they were running around with orders and unable to keep the restaurant clean.  The floors had food and garbage, and the bathrooms were filthy.  The bathrooms were a major one for me because the mess appeared to have been there all day. Wheelchair accessibility: You can get into the restaurant, order, and sit in a few of the tables that are closest to the door.  You cant easily get a wheelchair to the back to pick up your food, get condiments and drinks, or access the bathrooms due to the tables being in the way and the amount of skip the dishes drivers and other customers standing around waiting for their orders.  It is pure chaos in that area, but another customer offered help.

Much better than UK Five Guys. The Cajun chips were great and the way you can customise your burger is awesome. The monkey nuts option is a neat novelty as well, albeit a little messy. Definitely the best fast food franchise.
One of the juiciest burgers out there, dine in option not available during night as it is always packed. Excellent service!

I ordered the cheeseburger with regular fries and they were really tasty!!! Always wanted to try out this place because it seemed to be very popular and now I know why:) I think the price-performance ratio is also one of the best. Another plus is the fast service and that you can get free peanuts while waiting for your burger.
Fast service, food was ready in less then 10min. Best Burger Ive had all year. Will be back.

Honestly this is one of the best burger joints in Vancouver. Me and a friend have been going around and trying lots of different burger joints in Vancouver and 5 guys always hits better. Surprised for a  chain  style restaurant how much love goes into the food here! The staff at this particular location are always super friendly and helpful, and always offer us free nuts too! My favourite topping is the fresh jalapenos
Didnt know there was a 5 guys in the downtown...when we saw it , everything else was off the menue for lunch!  Just the best birthday lunch! Thanks red and white!
Karan T was one of the nicest cashiers I have ever had in a fast food establishment. Kind, polite, and helpful. Someone who definitely deserves a raise.
Best burger place in the world... cant get enough of their burgers. Also the cajun fries are amazing as well. Five guys beats all the other burger joints.

We had the classic cheese hamburger. We couldnt stop munching on it, it just blew our mind. Totally delicious. In addition, there is unlimited fill up for drinks and salted peanuts. Will definitely revisit.
I love having Five Guys in my mouth! Its so much fun. The cheese burgers are also good here. Food : 5/5
Cant go wrong with their Burgers and Cajun Fries! Quick and delicious what else do you need?
Tasty burgers, really nice staff, and enjoyed the peanuts while waiting for my food.

Great burger. Definitely enjoyed the visit. The fries were great at first but as it got colder, I simply wanted to get them off my plate as quickly as possible. Customer service was great though and I would highly recommend this location to anyone craving a burger.
Food is fresh. The guy in the back in charge of orders today at 7:20pm is super on point despite the place being busy.
Their burger is definitely the best among all the fast food burger places around. Its usually pretty busy, so Ive only gotten take out. Go all the way! So good!
Its an absolute star. The best burger in Vancouver. High quality, acceptable price, tasty food and friendly staff.
First time here, got their best burger and med fries, OOPS! It ended up being two meals for me but the price to food ratio was worth it. It was a good burger, Id come again.
Lovely food. A great burger joint with fountain drinks. The food and fries are more than enough to get you full.
Best burgers in Vancity

My favourite burger in Vancouver. It s a bit pricy but it s huge and very American style. Processed cheese and a soft bun. Unlimited peanuts in a barrel for the taking as well. The Cajun fries are very good and you can ask for sides of mayo for no charge. It s not trying to be something besides a basic juicy burger so if that s what you want this is the place!
To me, this is the best place to have a burger. Like homemade juicy patties with crispy fries and fantastic shakes. Have the bite!

Fast service, on pricier side for fast food but small fries and little burger are still big servings for just one person. Good staff, yummy food, was busy but still clean. Love going here when I want a quick bite between shops.
Amazing burguers, dont miss the chance to taste the spicy fries.
Five dudes is delicious. I suggest you get little fries instead of reg, they load the fries so heavy that little and reg size honestly feel the same Food : 5/5
Best burgers in town, I used skip the dishes and got my order early.
Great burgers, available in salad wrap if you want to limit your calories coming from carbs. Their spicy fries are soo good. Try it.
Really friendly staff. Since we dont have Five guys in Mexico I was craving for the chance of eating them again: delicious flavour, just as I recall. The best chain burgers!

My first time trying five guys and I love it, the burgers are fully loaded and probably one of the best burgers I have ever had. The fries are overflowing and are packed with flavour! Highly recommend
Very good burger and fries with minimum fuss,lots of great toppings, great service! Very basic interior design,retro style, would definitely be a regular here.

Really delicious burgers. The chips were not crispy enough and felt a little soggy. The burger was flavourful and just one bite is enough to let you know that they used quality ingredients in it. Only (minor) complaint is that the ingredients fell out quite easily so it was messy eating it. Toilet available on the premise. As others have mentioned, peanuts are available for you to help yourself too while waiting for your order.
Great food. A bit pricey for a Burger place but everything was large portions.

They went above and beyond.  I ordered two takeout burgers, one was mistakenly put as no toppings...my kids were hungry so they ate everything and found out there was no toppings...we went back and they gave us a new one immediately! Great service. Burgers and fries are great too!
One of the best burgers you can have in Vancouver. Burger are always made fresh. They are very generous with their fries portions. There are also free peanuts you may eat while you wait.
It was a little pricy ($33 for 2 burgers and a poutine) but man it was worth it. I <3 five guys. There was a lot of people and little to no sitting room when I got there.
The burgers are loaded and for the price it s amazing Also don t forget to enjoy their peanuts
Not the best Burger in BC but pretty good though. I recommend it
Excellent location for a classic burger joint. Simple and efficient. Excellent value as well. Staff is extremely friendly and helpful to make sure you have a great experience.

It is awesome when you find a staff that speaks the same language as you. That makes your visit easier and better to order food and hang out with friends. The location is good, but you have to find a spot to park on the street. Food

Why go to McDonalds when you can get a much better product for a few bucks more. My burger was fresh, delicious and the small fries I ordered were enough for 2 people. Bonus for the shelled peanuts to snack on while I watched the grill master make my food.

I was the last customer to be served , they were very polite and helpful, my burger was amazing and the spicy fries was so delicious. The place is filled with peanuts , not suitable for people with allergies
Its rare to get one burger place with real meat. Because its in downtown, its normal the presence of heavy drug users. Food : 5/5

I had an extraordinary experience at Five Guys in Robson St. Vancouver! The service and the food are noteworthy. The fries taste amazing. They have options for the size of the sandwich. I and my cohorts chose to have the little (smaller) portions.
Always busy but food and service are 10/10.

One of my favorite burgers in DT Vancouver, the prices are decent but the flavors of the burger is really good. The staff is always very kind even if they re very busy. They offer free many. Fries and poutine are really good.
Its a burger joint near the university. Great bacon burger, which was exactly what I wanted. A chain but a good one
I tried the burger here for the first time and I really liked it
More than just burgers, has awesome BLT!! Efficient and cordial service.
was great every time i go their it s always my fav
Best burger and fries anywhere.
Finally, I had this famous Burger. It was way better than I expected. Even though staff were super busy, they kept smiling. In my opinion, this is the best burger shop ever.
Very fast service. Its Five Guys not much to say here.
Food is always top notch. Delicious burgers and fries, a must-try!!
Everyone knows Five Guys is awesome! If you dont and youre reading this, its the burger and fries youre absolutely looking for. Get the double cheeseburger.
Great food and price . Hard to get a table :(

They are always very nice people working there. The food is made from scratch which makes it worth the money. The place is mostly busy but those ladies know how to handle a crowd. A hungry one for that. Food : 5/5
Very delicious burger. ALL TOPPINGS FREE, this is huge! Very good price. Burgers are medium size.
Absolutely amazing every time! Cant wait to go back!!
The security guard from sun star is great and deserves a honest raise takes care of every problem which isn t normal and remembers the customers when most employees don t even :) \ gora jatt
The atmosphere inside the restaurant is vibrant and lively, adding to the overall dining experience.

If you can order online I recommend it purely for wait times. The staff is wonderful whether you order online or in store! Just make sure if you have ordered online, dont be shy, walk up up to the serving counter and someone will notice you and ask for your online order pickup name !
How can you not love this burger! Double patty done to perfection.
Always good service and well priced. Gets pretty busy at this location though not always a seat.
Love it! Best fast food.. Gourmet fast food Id say!   and at a really great price too..
I have a peanut allergy and cannot eat at this establishment.
Five Guys is very few and the best fast food restaurant you can get real nutrition and no artificial fake trash like McDonald.
Delicious burger combo for a good price. Fast service and I like the style of the restaurant.

This place never disappoint,  first of all I want to mention the fries that they have. Freshly cut and fried in front of you they are so good the spicy ones are my favorite. The Pattys are made freshly. The whole kitchen is visible nothing is happening that you cant see. Customer service is also good places world Cup clean. If you are in downtown I highly recommend you guys try this. Their veggie sandwich all the way is my favorite
Nice burger! I order a little cheese burger, but I am so full after ate half ! And they got free peanut. Very special.
Im not a big fan of hamburgers because Im always hungry after eating them, but this place really surprised me, good flavour, quantity and quality for a fast food chain.
